"The fact that someone in the UK's west Midlands cannot look after a USB key is big news. According to the press, the lost key contains the potential means to access the tax details of over 12m UK residents, along with a manual for using Government Gateway and the source code. 1 This has strong echoes of the ‘disc in the post’ problem that enveloped Christmas 2007 for some of the incident management team at HRMC. Now that missing USB keys are ‘hot news’, I suspect there will be a flood of media reports about them over the next few months until they become so common they are no longer newsworthy."
